  "text": "## Datasource Plugin Query Path Architecture\n\nThe Grafana datasource plugin query path consists of three main components: the HTTP request handler, the plugin backend query dispatcher, and the response transformation.\n\n### 1. HTTP Query Request Handler\n**File:** `pkg/api/ds_query.go`\n\nThe entry point for datasource queries is the `QueryMetricsV2()` function in the HTTP server. This function:\n- Receives HTTP POST requests at `/api/ds/query` endpoint\n- Unmarshals the request into a `dtos.MetricRequest` DTO\n- Delegates to the query data service (`hs.queryDataService.QueryData()` or `QueryDataNew()`)\n- Transforms the response using `toJsonStreamingResponse()` which converts the `backend.QueryDataResponse` to JSON streaming format with appropriate HTTP status codes (200 OK or 207 Multi-Status)\n\n### 2. Query Service Dispatch (Plugin Backend Query Dispatch)\n**File:** `pkg/services/query/query.go`\n\nThe `ServiceImpl` implements the `Service` interface which handles query execution. The dispatch flow:\n\n**ServiceImpl.QueryData()** - Public entry point that calls:\n\n**ServiceImpl.queryData()** - Core implementation that:\n1. Calls `parseMetricRequest()` to parse queries and group them by datasource UID\n2. Handles expressions if present via `handleExpressions()` (delegates to expression service)\n3. For single datasource queries: calls `handleQuerySingleDatasource()`\n4. For multiple datasource queries: calls `executeConcurrentQueries()`\n\n**ServiceImpl.handleQuerySingleDatasource()** - Single datasource handler that:\n1. Constructs a `backend.QueryDataRequest` from parsed queries\n2. Gets the plugin context via `s.pCtxProvider.GetWithDataSource()`\n3. Routes to either:\n   - `s.pluginClient.QueryData()` for single-tenant flow (standard plugin backend)\n   - `qsDsClient.QueryData()` for multi-tenant/query-service flow\n\n**ServiceImpl.parseMetricRequest()** - Request parser that:\n1. Iterates through queries and resolves datasources from the cache\n2. Groups queries by datasource UID\n3. Converts query JSON and time ranges to backend query format\n4. Returns a `parsedRequest` with flattened queries organized by datasource\n\n### 3. Plugin Client Query Dispatch\n**File:** `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go`\n\nThe `Service.QueryData()` method implements the `plugins.Client` interface:\n1. Validates the request is not nil\n2. Looks up the plugin from the registry using `s.plugin(pluginID, pluginVersion)`\n3. Delegates to `p.QueryData()` on the resolved plugin\n4. Handles response transformation - sets RefID on frames if not already set\n5. Converts gRPC errors to domain-specific error types\n\n### 4. Plugin QueryData Handler\n**File:** `pkg/plugins/plugins.go`\n\nThe `Plugin.QueryData()` method:\n1. Gets the backend plugin client via `p.Client()`\n2. Delegates to the client's `QueryData()` method via gRPC\n\nThe backend plugin client (grpcplugin.ClientV2) communicates with the datasource plugin process via gRPC.\n\n### 5. Response Transformation\n**File:** `pkg/api/ds_query.go`\n\nThe `toJsonStreamingResponse()` function:\n1. Creates a response with HTTP status code 200 OK (or 207 Multi-Status if any errors in responses)\n2. Wraps the `backend.QueryDataResponse` in a JSON streaming response\n3. Sets appropriate status source context for downstream error tracking\n\n### Query Path Flow Summary\n\n```\nHTTP POST /api/ds/query\n  ↓\nQueryMetricsV2 (pkg/api/ds_query.go)\n  ↓\nServiceImpl.QueryData (pkg/services/query/query.go)\n  ↓\nServiceImpl.queryData\n  ├→ parseMetricRequest (parse & group by datasource)\n  ├→ handleExpressions (if expressions present)\n  └→ handleQuerySingleDatasource (or executeConcurrentQueries)\n  ↓\nService.QueryData (pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go)\n  ├→ plugin registry lookup\n  └→ Plugin.QueryData (pkg/plugins/plugins.go)\n  ↓\nBackend Plugin gRPC QueryData\n  ↓\nResponse transformation (frames RefID, error handling)\n  ↓\ntoJsonStreamingResponse (pkg/api/ds_query.go)\n  ↓\nHTTP Response (200 OK or 207 Multi-Status)\n```\n\n### Key Middleware and Context Setup\n\nAdditional important files involved in the query path:\n- **pkg/services/pluginsintegration/plugincontext/plugincontext.go** - Creates plugin context with datasource settings, user info, and authentication\n- **pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client.go** - gRPC client factory for backend plugins\n- **pkg/plugins/manager/registry/registry.go** - Plugin registry that maintains registered plugins\n\nThe query path integrates with multiple middleware layers for:\n- Request validation (RBAC, datasource access control)\n- Query caching\n- OAuth token forwarding\n- Cookie forwarding\n- Tracing and metrics collection\n"

